#X text 65 16 The number of output channels in is the maximum of the number of both inputs. If both are of the same size \, each input signal sets the delay time of a correspondent delay channel. In case the numbers mismatch \, the smaller wraps around until reaching the number of the bigger one. So a single delay time value sets the delay time of all inputs. Using more delay time inputs than the available number of inputs is useful for implementing a multitap delay., f 77;
